<TEXT>
black and hispanic inmates armed with 
homemade knives brawled at an overcrowded county jail thursday and 
12 were injured before guards restored order officials said 
one prisoner at the el cajon detention center was critically 
injured said jail commander ben mclaughlin 
he said the fight began about 430 pm between black and 
hispanic inmates at the jail 15 miles east of san diego where a 
similar racially motivated fight left four inmates injured dec 13 
inmates retreated to their cells when deputies entered the 
cellblock armed with electric stun guns a weapon that fires rubber 
bullets inmates were armed with handmade knives and other crude 
weapons mclaughlin said 
the brawl attributed to overcrowding and racial tensions 
occurred in a cellblock designed to hold 24 inmates but which held 
100 prisoners when the riot broke out mclaughlin said 
deputies saw a black inmate and a hispanic inmate arguing 
moments before their confrontation erupted into a largescale 
brawl mclaughlin said 
in this case it was blacks vs hispanics mclaughlin said 
i was a racial issue but were not sure yet what sparked it it 
just erupted without warning 
one injured inmate was transported by helicopter to sharp 
memorial hospital where he was listed in critical condition with 
head injuries said hospital spokeswoman melanie bruce she 
declined to release the inmates name 
two other inmates suffering head injuries were admitted to 
university of california san diego medical center said 
spokeswoman jane swett one was in serious condition and the other 
in fair condition she said declining to release their names 
at least nine other inmates suffering cuts scrapes and other 
minor injuries also were taken to various east san diego county 
hospitals for treatment 
it took deputies about 15 minutes to get the prisoners into 
their cells before deputies regained control of the cellblock 
mclaughlin said 
there is no damage to the cells they were really injuring 
themselves mclauglin said 
deputies with guard dogs were stationed around the jail exterior 
as a sheriffs helicopter with a spotlight circled overhead to 
guard against any possible escapes 
the detention facility is designed to hold 120 but housed 
slightly more than 500 prisoners thursday 
</TEXT>
