a 31yearold east german man has 
been arrested in west germany on suspicion of trying to recruit 
students to work for east germanys intelligence service 
authorities say 
the chief federal prosecutors office on wednesday identified 
the suspect as michael keiser of the east german city of halle 
keiser is suspected of spying for east germany since june the 
office said in a statement it said he had attempted to recruit 
englishspeaking university students and was arrested jan 18 in 
the central city of mannheim 
at the time of his arrest keiser was carrying false 
identification papers and a fake passport the statement said 
the statement did not specify the nature of the information 
gathered by keiser who remains in investigative custody pending 
completion of the investigation against him 
although the east german governmment has been dismantling the 
countrys secret police under growing opposition pressure west 
german officials have warned that east german agents are continuing 
to spy abroad 
