<TEXT>
chinas senior leader deng xiaoping has 
predicted the downfall of mikhail s gorbachev and the resurgence 
of soviet conservatives a newspaper reported today 
the south china morning post quoting unnamed chinese sources in 
beijing said deng last week told communist party leaders that the 
ethnic turmoil and separatist movements sweeping the soviet union 
are products of the soviet presidents reform program 
after gorbachev has fallen from power he will be replaced by 
the conservative faction deng was quoted as saying the 
85yearold chinese patriarch did not say when he expected the 
change 
deng under whose leadership chinas prodemocracy movement was 
crushed in june has resigned from all his party posts to make way 
for younger leaders but is still believed to be the most powerful 
man in china 
chinas hardline leaders have been alarmed by the bloody 
overthrow of communist dictator nicolae ceausescu in romania and 
democratic movements sweeping eastern europe 
