amnesty international today accused 
somalias government of arbitrarily imprisoning torturing and 
executing its citizens without a fair trial 
the londonbased human rights organization called on the 
government of president mohammed siad barre to establish a 
comprehensive program of legal and institutional reforms to end 
the abuses 
