in the year 
it called them a serious setback to human rights improvements 
made in the first half of 1989 when the government of the horn 
of africa country released more than 1000 political prisoners 
with its 13page report amnesty became the second international 
human rights organization to sharply criticize the siad barre 
regime this year 
earlier this month new yorkbased africa watch said the somali 
military had killed between 40000 and 50000 unarmed civilians in 
the past 19 months 
