the time being but would cut its troops by onethird 
czechoslovakia and poland also have announced force reductions 
despite the changes borsits said the warsaw pact and nato 
should remain as a stabilizing factor their loosening would 
upset the balance and would lead to incalculable consequences 
the unstated fear is of a unified germany 
former secretary of state henry a kissinger suggested in a 
recent television interview that moscow should maintain some 
position in eastern europe as a safety net if there should be a 
revival of german nationalism or expansionism the unification of 
east and west germany he said was inevitable 
