young children said better alternatives to standardized tests 
include teacher observation portfolios of student work and 
performances and exhibitions that are based on the curriculum 
too many young children today are retained a grade assigned 
to special classes or held out of school based on the results of 
readiness and achievement tests that have questionable predictive 
accuracy 
