<TEXT>
a new military navigation satellite 
is orbiting the earth as part of a network of spacecraft that guide 
bombers warships missiles and ground troops with precision 
accuracy 
an air force delta rocket boosted the 65 million navstar 
satellite into space wednesday night and officials reported 25 
minutes later that it was in a successful orbit ranging out to 
11000 miles high 
everything appears to have gone well with tonights launch 
reported capt ken warren the air force launch commentator 
it is the sixth in a series of advanced navstar satellites 
launched during the past year from cape canaveral by 1992 the air 
force plans to have 21 orbiting the earth to form a global system 
coded satellite signals guide us and allied military units 
such as ships planes submarines tanks and land forces with 
pinpoint accuracy in any weather 
civilian users such as planes and ships also have access to the 
navstar system through an open channel that gives them accuracies 
within 300 feet 
