the poet writer and scholar damaso alonso 
director emeritus of the royal academy of the spanish language has 
died after a long illness a family member said today he was 91 
alonso who had suffered from respiratory problems for the last 
three years died late wednesday at his home said the family 
member who asked not to be identified 
a poet of the socalled generation of 1927 that included 
federico garcia lorca and rafael alberti alonso was also an 
essayist considered among the countrys leading scholars of spanish 
literature 
in 1978 he was awarded spains miguel de cervantes prize 
considered the highest literary prize for spanishlanguage writers 
he received honorary degrees from oxford and the universities of 
bordeaux rome hamburg friburg lima and costa rica 
born in madrid he became professor of romanesque philosophy in 
the university of valencia and later at the university of madrid 
before going on to teach at universities in south america 
he became a member of the royal academy of the spanish language 
in 1945 and served four terms as its director from 196882 
his best known works included the volumes of poetry pure 
poems poems of the city 1921 and the sons of anger 1944 
and his collected poems man and god 1955 
