<TEXT>
legislation creating a cabinetlevel 
department of the environment is expected to move swiftly through 
congress with sponsors saying they hope to send it to president 
bush in time for signing on earth day in april 
bush endorsed the bipartisan legislation wednesday saying 
the environmental challenges that face america and the world are 
so important that they must be addressed from the highest level of 
our government 
his move drew praise from environmentalists and both democrats 
and republicans on capitol hill but several senators suggested the 
president must do more than elevate the status of the environmental 
protection agency to deal with the worlds environmental problems 
its not enough just to put an extra chair to the cabinet 
table said sen al gore dtenn who has been a past critic of 
the bush administrations actions on such environmental matters as 
global warming and atmospheric ozone depletion 
