<TEXT>
the associated press announced thursday that it 
is switching to electronic darkrooms as its basic photo receivers 
accelerating the conversion of the nations newspapers to 
photostream aps pictureaminute digital photo delivery highway 
in the third quarter of this year ap will begin replacing 
laserphoto receivers at 950 newspapers that receive ap photos with 
the ap leaf picture desk a microprocessorbased electronic 
darkroom developed by ap and leaf systems of natick mass said 
louis d boccardi ap president and general manager 
this is a major step into the electronic future for us and 
for our newspaper members boccardi said this revolutionizes 
picture handling the darkroom enormously improves photo 
reproduction quality and opens the door to production efficiencies 
and ultimately pagination of pictures in the nations newspapers 
he said that installation of the darkrooms would be done by 
region and would take two years from the start of the project 
ap announced plans for photostream in 1987 and has tested 
aspects of the highspeed digital collection and delivery system at 
newspapers during the past year a prototype transmitted photos 
from the world series and the malta summit and will be used at the 
super bowl 
the photostream delivery network incorporates a highcapacity 
satellite circuit and digital technology 
aps present laserphoto delivery system transmits black and 
white photos in nine minutes and color in 30 minutes photostream 
transmits black and white in less than one minute and color in less 
than three 
aps original photostream plans called for replacement of the 
current nineminute ap laserphoto receiver with a twominute 
receiver newspapers who wished to buy darkrooms could have done so 
as the ap experimented further with electronic darkrooms it 
became clear that we should opt for the technology of the future 
not an updated version of the technology of the past boccardi 
said 
john reid ap vice president and director of communications and 
technology said that photostream subscribers will have the option 
of receiving an expanded photo report or the same report they 
receive today the photostream report also will provide more color 
and a greater selection of photos 
if a paper chooses it can buy the ap vax picture desk a system 
that incorporates digital equipment corporations vax computer 
technology 
both the ap leaf picture desk and the ap vax picture desk 
include a disk storage device with the capacity for hundreds of 
images and a terminal with monitor and keyboard the electronic 
darkrooms will work with virtually all conventional scanning and 
screening devices and will have the capability with additional 
hardware of receiving the newspapers local pictures 
each system is fast and easy to use can handle analog and 
digital reception and can operate as a single workstation or be 
expanded with newspaperpurchased options to a network of 
editing stations storage and ports are also easily expandable with 
newspaperpurchased options both systems have output capability 
for both receivers and pagination systems reid said 
if a newspaper does not want an electronic darkroom ap will 
install its new twominute laserphoto receiver the newspaper also 
will have the option of purchasing a darkroom other than the ap 
leaf or ap vax picture desks 
we have a flexible system here said hal buell ap assistant 
general manager for newsphotos it will fit the kind of picture 
handling arrangement that individual newspapers want 
aps decision to use the electronic darkroom as its basic 
photo receiver opens the door to the world of electronic picture 
handling for our members buell said 
the relationship between ap and leaf systems began in 1988 when 
ap helped develop and became the exclusive distributor of the ap 
leafax 35 a portable negative transmitter 
the two companies decided recently to collaborate on the ap leaf 
picture desk the two companies also recently agreed to provide the 
ap leafspooler which allows a photographer to store and transmit 
pictures that have been processed in the ap leafax 35 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

