the bang is gradually going out of chinese new 
year as authorities in beijing cut the capitals firecracker supply 
for the third straight year and similar measures are being adopted 
in other cities 
traditionally the chinese greet the lunar new year which this 
year falls on saturday with a long deafening roar of 
firecrackers which are supposed to drive off evil spirits 
