firecracker sales 
ma zhengjia director of the beijing public security bureaus 
foreign affairs office said thursday that regulations on the sale 
transport and shooting off of firecrackers were enacted in 1986 to 
try to reduce the number of deaths injuries and fires caused by 
firecrackers each lunar new year or spring festival as the 
holiday is called in mainland china 
in 1987 251 people in beijing were killed or injured by 
firecrackers but the following year the figure was down to 26 he 
said adding that the number of fires went down from 224 in 1987 to 
22 last year 
but authorities this year may be more concerned about 
controlling the holiday celebrations after hundreds of thousands of 
disenchanted chinese took to the streets last spring calling for 
democracy and other changes martial law imposed in may was lifted 
only two weeks ago 
as before bans have been placed on setting off firecrackers at 
tiananmen square site of last springs prodemocracy protests and 
other public places that draw crowds including the railway station 
and airport but the number of restricted areas 610 is nearly 
double what it was two years ago 
ma insisted there was no connection between the regulations 
which he said were longstanding and last years prodemocracy 
movement which was crushed by troops who entered the city killing 
hundreds and perhaps thousands of people 
it has nothing to do with june 3 he said referring to the 
night the army marched into beijing 
as you can see for yourself our society is very stable right 
now the masses are happily preparing for the holiday the markets 
are abundently stocked with whatever you want to buy ma said 
store shelves in beijing still were wellstocked thursday two 
days before the new year 
one little boy just tall enough to see over the counter stood 
with his nose pressed to the glass case trying to decide whether to 
get pretty fireworks like the flash of lightning or two kicks 
of the feet or the traditional strings of red firecrackers that 
his father impatiently told him to choose 
the cheapest were 3footlong sparklers that went for about 3 
cents there were 2 bags of colorful animals and other toys that 
run in circles while spraying colorful sparks when lighted the 
most expensive were strings of 1000 firecrackers that cost about 
230 to 320 
buyers unhesitatingly paid between 4 and 6 and some said they 
planned to buy more 
im buying these for my two daughters said a man in his 30s 
after asking the clerk to show him fireworks appropriate for 
little girls 
