top musicians penned birthday greetings to 
wolfgang amadeus mozart some of them poetic and some in the dear 
mo vein in case the famous composer can somehow get the message 
on his perch up in harmony heaven 
from measure to measure each note is a treasure rhymed the 
cleveland quartet thank you mozart for giving an unsettled 
world so much joy passion and beauty which will enrich us 
forever contributed the tokyo string quartet 
mozart was born 234 years ago saturday the birthday messages 
from the likes of zubin mehta victor borge and the new york city 
opera were written to mark the day and to publicize a mozart series 
planned for 199192 at lincoln center for the performing arts they 
are being displayed on a large poster in front of the center 
violinist joshua bell 22 said dear mr mozart you have 
affected my life immensely happy birthday 
a somewhat older violinist glenn dicterow concertmaster of the 
new york philharmonic said a special thanks for your violin 
concertos and symphonie concertante 
david zinman music director of the baltimore symphony said 
that mozarts music provides me with hope and courage 
mehta music director of the new york philharmonic informed the 
composer that hes about to become the object of this centurys 
most ambitious musical project 
he referred to a 19month tribute set to begin a year from 
saturday at the performing arts center during which all of 
mozarts compositions will be performed the onetime child prodigy 
wrote more than 800 works before he died in 1791 at age 35 
the new york city opera penned a wish you were here message 
for its next season when susanna and figaro renew their vows 
pianist rudolph firkusny told mozart that he will always 
remain young wonderful and alive among us 
some of the messages added a note of humor 
soprano dawn upshaw said thanks for saving your best efforts 
for sopranos 
even though you only wrote one piece for english horn happy 
birthday anyway wrote the philharmonics tom stacy who of 
course plays english horn 
and comedianpianist borges message read in its entirety 
dear mo as you know ive always referred to you in my oneman 
show as a bust however i consider you one of the worlds most 
successful busts please dont get plastered on your birthday 
love victor borge 
