ava gardner who lived a hollywood sirens life of 
fast cars failed marriages and heated affairs but failed to find 
happiness in love or in her 60film movie career died thursday at 
her west london home she was 67 
paul mills a longtime friend who announced the death said she 
had been ill with pneumonia 
the darkhaired greeneyed actress born a farmers daughter 
fled hollywood for europe in the 1950s 
she complained the image i seem to have that im a 
loudmouthed temperamental oversexed sultry siren sometimes 
terrifies me 
miss gardner was married briefly to actor mickey rooney and to 
big band leader artie shaw and for six years to singer frank 
sinatra 
i loved them all she said of her husbands but i never 
understood any of them and i dont think they understood me 
she was a wonderful lady wonderful lady said burt 
lancaster who starred with her in the killers the film that 
launched her sex goddess image in 1946 
she was a very simple lady she used to come down to the beach 
with us and cook and play with the kids lancaster said from his 
home in los angeles 
she was probably the most beautiful woman i ever met sheer 
enchantment said donald sinden who appeared with her in 1953 in 
mogambo 
the film which also starred clark gable and grace kelly 
brought miss gardner her only academy award nomination 
the star of such films as on the beach night of the 
iguana show boat the barefoot contessa and the snows 
of kilimanjaro regarded herself as a simple country girl who 
would have traded all the glitter for one happy longlasting 
marriage 
thats what i grew up hoping to find one good man i could 
love and marry and cook for and make a home for who would stick 
around for the rest of my life she said in an interview with 
londons daily express in 1982 
i never found him 
she also had wellpublicized romances with billionaire howard 
hughes actors george c scott and robert mitchum spanish 
bullfighter luis miguel dominguin cuban playboy porfirio rubirosa 
and italian comedian walter chiari 
after leaving hollywood in 1958 she was sometimes seen dancing a 
passionate flamenco in madrid and survived two road accidents in 
the highpower cars she raced down narrow spanish roads 
ava lavinia gardner was born dec 24 1922 in grabtown nc 
the youngest of six children of cotton and tobacco farmer jonas 
gardner 
her father lost the farm when she was 2 and later he worked in a 
sawmill in newport news va where her mother mary elizabeth ran a 
boarding house 
when she was 18 she visited her older sister bea in new york 
beas husband photographer larry tarr shot dozens of pictures of 
her and displayed one in his studio 
barney dunham then a clerk in mgms new york legal department 
urged tarr to send some pictures to hollywood the result was a 
screen test and a 50aweek contract 
her first film role came in we were dancing in 1942 the 
year she married rooney he was 21 and she was 19 the union lasted 
20 months 
my heart is broken with the loss of my first love rooney 
said in a statement released in los angeles 
she met shaw at a hollywood nightclub they married in october 
1945 shaw took books to read on their honeymoon miss gardner 
later suffered a nervous breakdown and the marriage ended a year 
and a week after it began 
in 1950 she met sinatra who was married and mired in a career 
slump they were married in november 1951 and divorced in july 1957 
each was an only child she said of her husbands and each one 
was basically a musician highly talented and uh highly strung 
then rolling her eyes she added thats putting it mildly 
baby 
she moved permanently to london in 1968 
im one hollywood broad who hasnt taken the sleeping tablets 
tried to slash my wrists or kick a cop she told one interviewer 
london gave me back my sanity 
she complained to an interviewer on her 60th birthday the 
trouble was that i was a victim of image because i was promoted as 
a sort of siren and played all those sexy broads people made the 
mistake of thinking i was like that off the screen 
they couldnt have been more wrong i am pathologically 
shy i was a country girl and i still have a country girls rather 
simple ordinary values 
no one ever wanted to know the real me at all they preferred 
the myths the roaring lady who smashed champagne glasses and 
seduced bullfighters 
that was her role hardliving lady brett in the 1957 film 
version of ernest hemingways novel the sun also rises 
joseph mankiewicz who directed her as the wild spanish dancer 
in the barefoot contessa said in los angeles thursday i 
dont think ava ever put body and soul into her performance she 
put body and soul into living a life miss gardner said in 
announcing in 1958 she was quitting mgm the studio that brought 
her to hollywood in 1941 
mgm was never the right studio for me they never knew 
what to do with me most of the time they loaned me out 
in one of her last roles she appeared on the cbstv series 
knots landing in 1985 
mills said miss gardners body would be taken to smithfield 
nc for burial alongside her parents 
he said miss gardner had not felt completely healthy since 
suffering a stroke in 1986 and for three months had been unable to 
take her corgi dog for walks in hyde park 
she was joking last night mills said my wife is one of 
her oldest friends they were on the phone talking last night and 
she was a little bit sad because she wanted to be better 
a sister myra pearce of winstonsalem nc said miss 
gardners housekeeper called her early thursday to say the actress 
had died in her sleep 
