<TEXT>
a dynamite attack on the countrys main 
petroleum pipeline thursday caused an oil spill covering nearly two 
square miles and leaked thousands of barrels of crude into a 
mountain stream the state petroleum company ecopetrol reported 
an ecopetrol communique did not say who was responsible for the 
attack outside teorama but authorities believe it was almost 
certainly perpetrated by leftist guerrillas belonging to the 
national liberation army known as the eln 
the eln has claimed responsibility for 115 attacks against 
colombian petroleum facilities since 1986 in an effort to force the 
government to nationalize the industry 
the group called a halt to the attacks in the second half of 
1989 but renewed them this year to protest a hike in the domestic 
price of gasoline 
the ecopetrol communique said the blast near teorama would have 
serious ecological consequences because thousands of barrels of 
spilled crude flowed into a pristine stream that feeds the 
catatumbo river 
teorama is 260 miles north of the capital bogota 
thursdays attack was the third this year against the pipeline 
running from the cano limon oil field on the border with venezuela 
to the caribbean port of covenas near cartegena 
ecopetrol said it was stopping the flow of crude through the 
pipeline until a team could repair it 
