on top took off about 730 am pst 
it was a pretty sight said don haley a spokesman for the 
national aeronautics and space administration the sun was just 
up and it was glistening in the air 
the plane landed for a refueling stop at davismonthan air force 
base near tucson ariz about 1 hours later and at kelly air 
force base in san antonio texas about 310 pm for an overnight 
stop 
if weather permits the plane will refuel again friday at eglin 
air force base in florida before returning to the space center at 
cape canaveral 
one extra refueling stop was added to each day of the trip from 
california to florida because of extra weight added by the 
satellite the shuttle is transporting nasa spokeswoman pat 
phillips said in san antonio 
during the san antonio stop cool air will be blown on the 
shuttle to keep the cargo within specified temperature ranges she 
said 
columbia the oldest shuttle landed at this mojave desert 
military base at 135 am pst saturday after a record 10day 
21hour mission 
the shuttles fivemember crew deployed a navy communications 
satellite then retrieved the 11ton 30footlong long duration 
exposure facility a science satellite that soon would have burned 
up in earths atmosphere if it had not been plucked from its 
decaying orbit 
the ldef will be removed from columbias cargo bay after arrival 
at kennedy space center nasa will begin work immediately to 
prepare columbia for its next launch scheduled may 3 
the next shuttle mission is scheduled to start feb 22 when 
