<TEXT>
the food and drug administration on thursday 
cautioned consumers against buying potentially dangerous 
ltryptophan dietary supplements distributed nationally by a 
california company 
the company nutricology inc of san leandro calif which 
also markets under the name of allergy research group has not 
complied with an urgent fda recall request the agency said 
a woman answering the companys telephone refused to relay 
repeated calls to an official of the company or a supervisor in 
charge 
the agency said 334 other manufacturers repackers and 
distributors have complied with the nov 17 request for recall of 
products that would result in a total dietary intake of 100 
milligrams or more of ltryptophan a day 
the fda requested the recall because ltryptophan an amino 
acid has been linked to eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome which is 
marked by severe muscle and joint pain swelling of the arms and 
legs skin rash and sometimes fever 
the centers for disease control has reports of 1143 cases of 
the syndome including nine deaths one of which has been 
confirmed to have been clearly associated with ltryptophan 
cases have been reported in all 50 states the district of columbia 
and puerto rico 
public health experts have not been able to identify a specific 
lot brand manufacturer or supplier of the supplement as the cause 
of the outbreak they also have been unable to identify a specific 
chemical or microbial contaminant that could be responsible the 
fda said 
the ltryptophan products made by the company are 
ltryptophan capsules 500 milligrams 100 capsules to a 
bottle under the allergy research group label 
tryptophan prn 350 milligrams 30 capsules to a bottle 
under the nutricology and allergy research labels 
free aminos 750 milligram capsules and free aminos without 
cystine and cysteine both in 100capsule bottles and free aminos 
powder in 50 and 100 gram bottles all under both labels 
the fda said the company responded to the november recall 
request by saying they may recall their products but that 
company officials have refused to furnish the agency with any proof 
they have begun a recall 
