<TEXT>
cuba said thursday it temporarily suspended 
pulling its troops out of angola until it gets a satisfactory 
explanation for an attack by a usbacked force that cuba said 
killed seven of its soldiers this week 
a foreign ministry statement quoted by the cuban government 
news agency prensa latina said the unita attack last sunday also 
killed three angolan soldiers it said cuba took its action jointly 
with the angolan government 
the dispatch from havana was monitored in mexico city 
the statement said the united states was providing expert advice 
to unita forces which it called armed terrorist bands 
it said cuba will not let these bands attack cuban military 
personnel and sabotage the accords so laboriously worked out among 
cuba angola and south africa to end the angolan conflict 
in a statement issued thursday from their bush headquarters at 
jamba southeast angola the rebels said that they did not know 
cubans were guarding the position under attack they said havana 
failed to distribute information on its troop positions 
cuba called it a deliberate act of terrorism with the full 
knowledge that cuban personnel were there 
according to a cuban diplomat in luanda capital of angola who 
spoke on condition of anonymity earlier thursday only cuban 
civilians and no soldiers left the country in the previous 24 hours 
an estimated 50000 cuban troops supporting marxist angola in a 
15year civil war with the national union for the total 
independence of angola began a unmonitored withdrawal in january 
1989 under the accord signed in new york 
about half of cubas forces had been withdrawn so far per 
schedule and all were due to leave by mid1991 
in return south africa agreed to halt support for the rebels 
and grant independence to angolas southern neighbor namibia 
unita was not a party to the new york accords but pledged not to 
attack the cubans as they withdrew 
state department spokeswoman margaret tutwiler said in 
washington the administration is making inquiries of cuba to 
clarify the situation 
she said failure to continue the troop withdrawal in 
accordance with the schedule established by the accords will call 
into question the commitment of cuba and angola to the 
search for peace in southwest africa 
assistant secretary herman cohen said thursday he would try to 
speak to all sides involved in the incident in the next few days 
thursdays cuban statement said five cuban soldiers and six 
angolan soldiers also were wounded in unitas attack at a water 
purification plant in the hanha valley about 155 miles south of 
luanda and 13 angolan civilians were killed and 27 wounded 
members of the un monitoring force said earlier the attack 
killed four cubans and wounded seven 
angola has been embroiled in civil strife since it became 
independent from portugal 15 years ago with unita waging an 
effective bush war against the popular movement for the liberation 
of angola or mpla the marxist party in power 
cuba sent troops in 1976 to help angola fight the unita 
guerrillas who were backed by the united states and south africa 
cuban politburo member jorge risquet said two years ago that 
1000 cubans had died mostly from disease accidents and 
terrorist attacks rather than combat western estimates are 
that 5000 cubans died in angola and unita says the figure is 
higher 
there are 1000 soviet military advisers involved in planning 
and supervising combat operations according to western estimates 
the united states and the unita rebels have contended that 
government forces launched a major offensive a month ago to try to 
capture a strategic rebel stronghold 
