involving the two sides and federal mediator ben youtsey 
it was the second bargaining session since a threeyear offer 
without any general pay raises or bonuses after the first year was 
rejected on a 69 percent vote dec 18 a recess to review positions 
on each side followed a meeting jan 10 
the revised offer includes a 3 percent pay increase in the first 
year and productivity bonuses of 10 percent of gross pay in the 
first year 5 percent in the second and 4 percent in the third 
in addition money equal to 2 percent of all salaries in the 
unit is reserved for additional selective pay increases every six 
months with the entire pool to be spent 
