futures prices of wheat and soybeans fell sharply 
thursday on the chicago board of trade in a late selloff linked to 
improving crop weather and slack demand for feed grains both 
domestically and abroad 
corn and oat futures also closed lower 
a flurry of grain and soybean buying late last year and earlier 
this month has filled delivery pipelines resulting in a demand 
lull 
ports in the soviet union are reportedly jammed with nearly 3 
million metric tons of imported grain waiting to be unloaded 
in the wheat market in particular the chance for doing any 
significant business is limited and were in a liquidating 
market said jerry zusel manager of trading floor operations for 
the brokerage balfour maclaine corp 
