finance the savings and loan bailout only because the term was 40 
years too long for us 
we havent sold any us bonds lately and well continue 
to buy he said 
but nogami added that with japanese interest rates rising 
japanese bonds are fairly attractive especially since they 
carry no currency exchange risk for japanese investors 
the central bank has raised its official discount rate the 
interest it charges commercial banks three times since last may 
bringing it to 425 percent from 25 percent in moves aimed at 
bolstering the yen and heading off inflation 
in turn the yield of government bonds calculated on the basis 
of price plus interest rate in secondary trading has shot up 
but world market turmoil and the political climate at home have 
kept japanese funds from being repatriated in large sums said 
