chairman john t dorrance jr said it was putting its 17 percent 
stake in the business up for sale and planned to seek a price per 
share significantly in excess of current market value 
but the companys board reaffirmed its intention to resist 
pressure to put campbell on the auction block 
we have concluded that now is not the time to pursue a sale or 
merger of the company the board said we are convinced that 
maintaining the companys independence is the superior means of 
maximizing the wealth of the companys shareholders over the long 
term 
the board holding its regular monthly meeting at the companys 
corporate headquarters in camden endorsed a plan designed to 
leverage the extensive brand power of campbell soup co and to 
deliver the financial results needed to build longterm shareholder 
wealth 
campbell provided no specific details david hackney a company 
spokesman declined to elaborate 
